    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400 - DESCRIPTION - FENDER
        EXTENSIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FENDER EXTENSIONS</title>
        <para>Fender Extensions are an integral part of the fender system on the 41/42/43/4400 series vehicles. The
            fender extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. This protects the lower front
            of the cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, and it also keeps the step cleaner (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900309">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900309" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900309.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. 41/42/43/4400 Series Fender Extension</caption>
